202
00:20:32,057 --> 00:20:34,518
[SPEAKER_01]: I'm not aware of any statistics.

203
00:20:34,558 --> 00:20:49,786
[SPEAKER_01]: The only thing I comment on is that my experience is that having a ward counselor gives you a point person, one individual who you feel is the person you can go to because they represent your ward, your neighborhood.

204
00:20:51,653 --> 00:20:54,016
[SPEAKER_01]: but I don't have any statistics to back that up.

205
