[SPEAKER_08]: We had a public information session on October 19th.

1285
01:54:16,969 --> 01:54:22,433
[SPEAKER_08]: Our turnout in the hall was not very good, but we did have a good number on Zoom, and we had a good discussion.

1286
01:54:22,453 --> 01:54:27,296
[SPEAKER_08]: So thanks to everybody who participated and worked on that.

1287
01:54:29,238 --> 01:54:37,123
[SPEAKER_08]: We had discussed survey outreach on election day, and I guess that's sort of along with what Eunice was talking about, just outreach in general.

1288
01:54:37,464 --> 01:54:39,345
[SPEAKER_08]: We do have one more month for the survey.

1289
01:54:40,458 --> 01:54:42,239
[SPEAKER_08]: So whatever people can do would be great.

1290
01:54:43,459 --> 01:54:47,001
[SPEAKER_08]: Our next meeting is on December 7th, as usual.

1291
01:54:48,021 --> 01:54:51,102
[SPEAKER_08]: And people who volunteered for subcommittees will be hearing about that.

1292
01:54:51,122 --> 01:54:56,405
[SPEAKER_08]: Does any member from the public have any comment at this point?

1293
01:55:00,226 --> 01:55:03,288
[SPEAKER_08]: Okay, so I think we're gonna wrap up.

1294
01:55:03,968 --> 01:55:05,368
[SPEAKER_08]: I'll make a motion to adjourn.

1295
01:55:05,689 --> 01:55:06,309
[SPEAKER_08]: Thank you, Maury.

1296
01:55:06,349 --> 01:55:06,849
[SPEAKER_08]: Second.

1297
01:55:07,449 --> 01:55:07,769
[SPEAKER_06]: Second.

1298
01:55:08,290 --> 01:55:08,850
[SPEAKER_08]: All in favor?

1299
01:55:09,641 --> 01:55:11,026
[SPEAKER_06]: Thanks, everybody.

1300
01:55:11,046 --> 01:55:11,829
[SPEAKER_08]: Wait a minute.

1301
01:55:11,869 --> 01:55:14,999
[SPEAKER_06]: Happy Thanksgiving everyone.

1302
01:55:15,019 --> 01:55:15,581
[SPEAKER_06]: Happy Thanksgiving.

1303
01:55:15,601 --> 01:55:17,367
[SPEAKER_09]: Happy Thanksgiving to all.

